{"textColorIndex":1,"bgColorIndex":0,"note":"<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901580\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909542\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909542\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; padding: 10px; margin: auto; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>The Impact of Values, Culture, and Ethics<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\">In this module, we will explore the impact of values, attitudes, emotions, and culture on management and delve into the importance of ethics and social responsibility in business. Understanding these key concepts will better equip you to navigate the complex management world and make decisions that align with your personal and organizational values. The readings from<span>&nbsp;<\/span><em>Contemporary Management<\/em><span>&nbsp;<\/span>(Chapters 3 and 4) and<span>&nbsp;<\/span><em>Love as a Business Strategy<\/em><span>&nbsp;<\/span>(Chapters 3 and 4) will provide a solid foundation for understanding these key concepts.<\/p>\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\">As you progress through the module, consider how your values, attitudes, and cultural background influence your approach to management. Reflect on the ethical dilemmas you may face as a manager and how you can promote a socially responsible organizational culture.<\/p>\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><em>Need Support? Visit the <a title=\"Post your questions here\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78163\" data-course-type=\"discussions\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78163\" data-api-returntype=\"Discussion\">Course Q&amp;A Discussion Board<\/a><\/em><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<hr \/>\n<p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><em>Time Commitment: Approximately 4 Hours<\/em><\/p>\n<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901584\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909535\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909535\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Learning Objectives<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p><strong>Through active engagement in this module, learners should be able to:<\/strong><\/p>\n    <ul>\n        <li><strong>Describe<\/strong> enduring values and attitudes which influence how managers \"manage.\" (CLO1)<\/li>\n        <li><strong>Identify <\/strong>the sources of managerial ethics. (CLO2)<\/li>\n        <li><strong>Summarize<\/strong> why behaviors create culture. (CLO4)<\/li>\n        <li><strong>Identify <\/strong>why inclusion is a vital component of culture. (CLO4)<\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901585\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909544\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909544\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Learning Materials&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p><em>The following carefully curated materials are designed to help you solidly understand this module's key concepts and principles.<\/em><\/p>\n    <h4><strong>Reading(s)<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <ul>\n        <li><strong>Contemporary Management<\/strong><\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n    <ul>\n        <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n            <ul class=\"list-disc pl-8 space-y-2 -mt-1\">\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 3: Values, Attitudes, Emotions and Culture<\/li>\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 4: Ethics and Social Responsibility<\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n        <\/li>\n        <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n            <div style=\"padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px;\">\n                <details>\n                    <summary style=\"cursor: pointer;\"><em>Chapter Summaries<\/em><\/summary>\n                    <div style=\"padding: 5px 15px;\">\n                        <p><strong>Contemporary Management<\/strong><\/p>\n                        <ul>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 3 Values, Attitudes, Emotions, and Culture.<\/strong> This chapter focuses on the manager as a feeling, thinking human being. It starts by describing enduring personality characteristics that influence how managers \"manage,\" as well as how they view other people, their organizations, and the world around them. It also discusses how managers' values, attitudes, and moods play out in organizations, shaping organizational culture. This chapter provides a strong appreciation of how the personal characteristics of managers influence the process of management in general and organizational culture in particular.<\/li>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 4 Ethics and Social Responsibility.<\/strong> This chapter examines the nature of the obligations and responsibilities of managers and the companies they work for toward the people and society who are affected by their actions. First, the nature of ethics and the source of ethical problems are discussed. Next, the major groups of people, or stakeholders, who are affected by the decisions that companies make are examined. Then, four rules or guidelines that managers can use to decide if a specific business decision is ethical or unethical are studied. Finally, the sources of managerial ethics and reasons why it is important for a company to behave in a socially responsible manner are discussed.<\/li>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/details>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/li>\n        <li>\n            <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><strong>Love as a Business Strategy<\/strong><\/p>\n            <ul class=\"list-disc pl-8 space-y-2 -mt-1\">\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 3: Behavior Eats Culture for Lunch<\/li>\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 4: Inclusion<\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n        <\/li>\n        <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n            <div style=\"padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px;\">\n                <details>\n                    <summary style=\"cursor: pointer;\"><em>Chapter Summaries<\/em><\/summary>\n                    <div style=\"padding: 5px 15px;\">\n                        <p><strong>Love as a Business Strategy<\/strong><\/p>\n                        <ul>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 3. Behavior Eats Culture for Lunch.<\/strong> Groups are made of individuals. As such, cultures are the result of individual behaviors. Each day, the behaviors of every single team member serve to either strengthen relationships or destroy them. And as their relationships go, so goes the organizational culture. The healthier the relationships, the healthier the culture.<\/li>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 4. Inclusion.<\/strong> In companies that don't explicitly emphasize inclusion, many team members feel that aspects of who they are might not be welcome or appreciated - as if they aren't allowed to be their full selves at work. As a result, they hold back important parts of themselves that could potentially add value to the organization. A culture rooted in inclusion, however, enables everyone to contribute at a high level.<\/li>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/details>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n    <h4><strong>Multimedia<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <ul>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" title=\"Link\" href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/talks\/simon_sinek_how_great_leaders_inspire_action\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How Great Leaders Inspire Action<\/a> [18:35 minutes]<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/talks\/shawn_achor_the_happy_secret_to_better_work\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Happy Secret to Better Work<\/a> [12:20 minutes]<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/www.loveasabusinessstrategy.com\/podcast\/love-as-a-business-strategy-with-ripple\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Love as a Business Strategy with Ripple<\/a> [23:26 minutes]<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/talks\/luvvie_ajayi_jones_get_comfortable_with_being_uncomfortable\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Get Comfortable with Being Uncomfortable<\/a> [10:45 minutes]<\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901586\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909539\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909539\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Tasks to Complete or Submit<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p><em>Completing the following tasks and assignments is crucial for demonstrating your understanding, applying your knowledge, and engaging with your peers and instructor.<\/em><\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\" style=\"display: flex; align-items: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; margin-right: 10px;\">ðŸ“š<\/span><strong>Engage with Course Content<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Read the assigned chapters from Contemporary Management and Love as a Business Strategy to build a strong foundation in management and leadership principles. Watch the provided videos on leadership and management to gain insights from real-world examples and expert perspectives.<\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\" style=\"display: flex; align-items: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; margin-right: 10px;\">ðŸ§©<\/span><strong>Assess Your Understanding<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Complete the <a title=\"Week #2 Quiz (CM Chapters 3-4, LAABS Chapters 3-4)\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140561\" data-course-type=\"quizzes.next\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140561\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Module 2 Quiz <\/a>to test your knowledge of the key concepts and principles covered in this module. The quiz is designed to reinforce your learning and provide feedback on areas for improvement. <strong>Due:<\/strong><\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\" style=\"display: flex; align-items: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; margin-right: 10px;\">ðŸ’¬<\/span><strong>Participate in Discussion<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Contribute to the <a title=\"Module 2 Discussion Forum\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78161\" data-course-type=\"discussions\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78161\" data-api-returntype=\"Discussion\">Module 2 Discussion<\/a> by sharing your thoughts, experiences, and questions about the course content. Engage with your classmates' posts to foster a collaborative learning environment. <strong>Due:<\/strong> The initial post is due Thursday; the peer responses are due Sunday.<\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸŒŸ <\/span><strong>Continue Working on Creating a Fictitious Company with Trello<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Remember to collaborate with your team on the ongoing <a title=\"Creating a Fictitious Company with Trello\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/142488\" data-course-type=\"assignments\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/142488\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Creating a Fictitious Company with Trello<\/a> assignment. Regularly communicate, assign tasks, and monitor progress to ensure a successful completion by the end of Module 6.<\/p>\n    <hr \/>\n    <h4><span><strong>Engage with Your Instructor and Peers<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n    <p style=\"border-left: 4px solid #e45424; padding-left: 10px;\"><span><strong>Optional Zoom Session<\/strong>: During Modules 1, 3, and 6, you will have the option to join a LIVE Zoom discussion, which will replace this week's online discussion points if you attend. If you come prepared and participate fully in the Zoom discussion sessions, you will not be required to complete the Discussion Forum for this week, as this will replace it for you.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<hr \/>\n<div style=\"background-color: #f2f4f8; color: #374a67; padding: 25px; width: 100%;\">\n    <h2 style=\"background-color: #e45424; color: #4e606a; padding: 25px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"color: #141414;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">Summary<\/span> <span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">of This Module's Learning Tasks<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/h2>\n    <div class=\"two-col-panels\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n        <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"col-sm card bg-light\">\n                <ul>\n                    <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n                        <ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\n                            <li>\n                                <p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Monday<\/strong>: Engage with this Module's Content<\/span><\/p>\n                            <\/li>\n                            <li>\n                                <p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Wednesday<\/strong>: Complete Module 2 Quiz<\/span><\/p>\n                            <\/li>\n                            <li>\n                                <p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;